Your script is solid and will produce a cockpit-ready JSON with per-category summaries and a global summary. To make it “best file” quality and include as much media as possible, here are targeted upgrades you can apply without changing the overall structure.

---

### Improvements for completeness and speed

- **Add file-type breakdown per category:**
  This shows counts per extension (e.g., .jpg vs .png, .mp3 vs .flac).

- **Record source root and category for each file:**
  Helps you trace origin and build filters in TwinHelm.

- **Skip directories explicitly:**
  Use `-File` to speed up traversal.

- **Harden against path/permission issues:**
  Wrap collection in try/catch and continue on errors.

- **Optionally expand video/audio formats:**
  Add common camera/RAW and container types.

